## When to use
When you need to inspect and understand detailed information about your system's individual CPU cores or processors over time.

## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `mpstat` command. Common advanced options include `-P ALL` for monitoring all available CPUs, `-w 1 -t` for updates every second with timestamps, which is useful for tracking resource usage over time. For continuous monitoring of CPU statistics by core or processor, you can use `mpstat -P ALL -w 1`.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "mpstat -P ALL -w 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run an `mpstat` command that monitors detailed CPU usage of all available cores and processors every second.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has installed and configured the necessary utilities for running shell commands.
- Be aware of the interval duration when using continuous monitoring as it can generate a large amount of output quickly.